# quack-auth project conventions

**Source of truth** for coding and layout conventions in this repo.

When the Developer states a **new convention** (or you extend an existing section here):

1. Update **this file** with the full convention text.
2. Add a **one-line pointer** in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) only ‚Äî do not duplicate detail there.
3. **Update related Docusaurus docs in the same branch/PR** ‚Äî **required**, not optional. See [Convention ‚Üí docs map](#convention--docs-map) below and [`.cursor/rules/docusaurus-docs.mdc`](./docusaurus-docs.mdc). Run `pnpm nx build DOCS` after doc edits.

### Convention ‚Üí docs map

| Convention area | Update these docs (minimum) |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| FE (HTTP client, styling, store, routing, ‚Ä¶) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/FE/` |
| BE (modules, filters, validation, routes, ‚Ä¶) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/be/` |
| Mongoose / DB | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/mongodb.md` |
| Shared libs (`libs/dtos`, `libs/qu-constants`, `BE_ROUTES`, ‚Ä¶) | Relevant `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/*.md` **and** setup page if cross-cutting (e.g. `06-nestjs-zod.md`) |
| Setup / tooling / git / Husky / env | Matching `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/NN-*.md` |
| AI policy / agent workflow | `apps/DOCS/docs/ai/policy.md` + root `AI.md` when judgement calls matter |

**Do not** land convention-only rule changes without the matching doc page(s). If a convention spans FE + BE (e.g. `BE_ROUTES`), update **both** app docs.

## Shared DTOs (`libs/dtos/src/lib/<domain>/`)

Organize by **domain folder** (e.g. `user/`, not flat files at `lib/` root unless legacy).

| Suffix | Purpose | Example |
| ------ | ------- | ------- |
| **`.model.ts`** | Zod mirror of a **persisted** Mongoose model (stored shape only; no plaintext passwords) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/user.model.ts` |
| **`.dto.ts`** | Flow/API schemas (signup, login, responses, ‚Ä¶) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/signup.dto.ts` |

- **Model DTO** (`.model.ts`) reflects what is stored in the database ‚Äî not plaintext passwords or other transient input shapes.
- **Other DTOs** (`.dto.ts`) hold API/input validation (e.g. signup with plaintext password rules).
- Reuse shared Zod building blocks inside a domain (e.g. `password.schema.ts`) when multiple DTOs need the same rules ‚Äî **do not invent new suffixes** (e.g. no `.fields.ts`; Developer reverted `user.fields.ts` from a `/simplify` pass).
- Some duplication between `.model.ts` and `.dto.ts` is acceptable; do not extract field schemas into unofficial file types.
- NestJS wraps shared schemas with `createZodDto` in `apps/BE` ‚Äî keep wrappers in sync when adding schemas (see `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/06-nestjs-zod.md`).

## Mongoose (`mongoose/models/<domain>/`)

Per domain, always three files:

| File | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| **`*.schema.ts`** | Mongoose schema + `model()` registration |
| **`*.model.ts`** | Repository interfaces (`IUser`, `IUserDocument`, ‚Ä¶) |
| **`*.paths.ts`** | Field path constants for queries, projections, and schema keys |

### Why `*.paths.ts`?

**Never hard-code field strings** in queries ‚Äî import from `*.paths.ts` so renames touch one file.

Example:

```ts
import { UserPaths } from '@quack/mongoose/models/user';

UserModel.findOne({ [UserPaths.email]: email });
```

### Mongoose directory (root)

```
mongoose/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ client.ts          # DB connection (ENV_KEYS, E2E URI switch)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ models/            # domain folders (user/, ‚Ä¶)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fixtures/          # test/dev fixture data
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tsconfig.json
```

## FE styling (Tailwind v4)

- **Nx scaffold** shipped Tailwind **v3** (`tailwind.config.js` + PostCSS); FE is migrated to **v4** (`tailwindcss@4`, `@tailwindcss/vite`).
- **Vite plugin** ‚Äî `@tailwindcss/vite` in `apps/FE/vite.config.mts` (not PostCSS `tailwindcss` plugin).
- **CSS-first theme** ‚Äî `apps/FE/src/styles.css`: `@import "tailwindcss"`, `@import "tw-animate-css"`, `@theme inline` for shadcn tokens; no `apps/FE/tailwind.config.js`.
- **shadcn CLI** ‚Äî `apps/FE/components.json` with `"config": ""`; add components via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add ‚Ä¶` from `apps/FE`.

