## FE HTTP client (`apps/FE/src/api/`)

- **One shared axios instance** ‚Äî `axiosConfig.ts` exports the default client; **do not** call `axios.create()` elsewhere in FE.
- **`baseURL`** ‚Äî from `VITE_API_URL` via `ENV_KEYS` (see `.env.example`); never hard-code API hosts in FE.
- **Import** ‚Äî `import api from '@/api/axiosConfig'` (or relative `../axiosConfig` under `api/services/`).
- **`handleError.ts`** ‚Äî normalizes `unknown` / `AxiosError` into `ErrorResponse` from `@shared/dtos`; axios-specific codes/messages live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/axios.constants.ts` (`AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`).
- **`axiosBaseQuery.ts`** ‚Äî RTK Query `BaseQueryFn` wrapping the shared axios instance; maps failures to `{ error: ErrorResponse }`.
- **`setupAxiosInterceptors.ts`** ‚Äî response interceptor: 401 ‚Üí single-flight `POST /auth/refresh` ‚Üí retry; refresh 401 ‚Üí `resetApp()` + `authApi.util.resetApiState()` + `persistor.purge()` + hard redirect to login. Invoked from `store.ts` after `configureStore`.
- **Request CSRF** ‚Äî mutating-method CSRF header stays in `axiosConfig.ts` request interceptor only.
- **`services/`** ‚Äî optional domain axios call sites for non-RTK flows; auth HTTP lives in RTK Query `authApi` instead. Import `BE_ROUTES` from `@shared/constants` ‚Äî **no magic route strings**.
- **`services/index.ts`** ‚Äî barrel re-export when domain services exist.

## FE Redux store (`apps/FE/src/store/`)

| Path | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| `api/authApi.ts` | RTK Query `createApi` ‚Äî auth HTTP (`register`, `login`, `logout`, `getMe`) via `axiosBaseQuery` |
| `api/quackApi.ts` | RTK Query `createApi` ‚Äî non-auth quack greeting (`quack` query, `POST /quack`) via `axiosBaseQuery` |
| `slices/*.ts` | Client session state (e.g. `auth.user`); **no `createAsyncThunk`** for auth HTTP |
| `root-reducer.ts` | `combineReducers` + `RESET_APP` wrapper (`appReducer`) |
| `reset.ts` | `resetApp()` action for full store reset on session death |
| `persist.config.ts` | Blacklist `authApi` cache; whitelist persist **`auth.user` only** via `createTransform` |
| `store.ts` / `hooks.ts` | Store + typed `useAppDispatch` / `useAppSelector`; `authApi.middleware`; calls `setupAxiosInterceptors` |

### Auth split (`authApi` + `authSlice`)

- **`authApi`** ‚Äî HTTP only; paths from `BE_ROUTES`; export generated hooks (`useRegisterMutation`, ‚Ä¶).
- **`authSlice`** ‚Äî `user: AuthUser | null`; `resetAuth` reducer; `extraReducers` matchers on `register` / `login` / `getMe` fulfilled ‚Üí set `user`; `logout` fulfilled ‚Üí clear `user`.
- **Axios refresh** ‚Äî not RTK Query; direct `api.post` in interceptor so store‚Üîapi wiring stays one-way.

### Slice hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/`)

- One hook per slice (e.g. `useAuth.ts`) ‚Äî **unified interface** exposing slice state (`user`, `isAuthenticated`) and `resetAuth`.
- Re-export RTK Query auth hooks from the slice-hook module (or import from `@/store/api/authApi` in page hooks).
- **Developer rationale:** when slice shape changes, update a few slice-hook files instead of many consumers across pages and components.
- Slice hooks are for **session state + reset** ‚Äî page hooks call RTK Query mutation hooks directly for auth HTTP.

## FE layered data flow

```
RTK Query authApi (axiosBaseQuery) ‚Üí authSlice matchers ‚Üí Slice hook ‚Üí Component logic hook ‚Üí UI
Axios interceptor (401 refresh) ‚Äî shared axios instance, benefits all RTK Query requests
```

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
| ----- | -------- | -------------- |
| **RTK Query API** | `store/api/authApi.ts` | Auth HTTP via `axiosBaseQuery` + `BE_ROUTES` |
| **Redux slice** | `store/slices/` | Client session (`user`); matchers sync from API responses |
| **Slice hook** | `hooks/slices/` | Typed facade over slice state + `resetAuth`; re-exports mutation hooks |
| **Page context** | `pages/<Page>/` or `contexts/` | **`fetch*` orchestration only** ‚Äî e.g. `ProtectedRoute` calls `lazyGetMe()` |
| **Component logic** | `useComponentName.ts` next to `ComponentName.tsx` | RHF + RTK Query mutations; local handlers |
| **UI component** | `ComponentName.tsx` | Presentational markup; minimal logic |

### Rules

- **Auth HTTP** ‚Äî RTK Query mutations/queries, not `createAsyncThunk`.
- **Page context / route guards:** `fetch*` effects live in route wrappers or page context only; use `useEffectEvent` for effect callbacks ‚Äî do not put those callbacks in dependency arrays.
- **Component logic:** no `fetch*` effects except via route guards; call RTK Query mutation hooks for register/login/logout.
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + `zodResolver` + shared DTOs from `@shared/dtos`; `useForm<z.input<typeof Schema>, unknown, z.output<typeof Schema>>` when defaults/transforms differ; child form components match parent input type.
- **Cleanup:** `resetAuth` / `RESET_APP` on session death; persist only `auth.user` (blacklist RTK Query cache).

## FE pages (`apps/FE/src/pages/<Page>/`)

- One folder per page (e.g. `pages/auth/Login/`, `pages/auth/Signup/`): `Page.tsx` (UI) + `usePage.ts` (component logic hook).
- **Routing** uses `react-router` (`react-router-dom`): `<BrowserRouter>` in `main.tsx`, `<Routes>` + global `<Toaster/>` in `app/app.tsx`. Path segments live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/routes.constants.ts` (`FE_ROUTES`, `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`) ‚Äî use them in `<Route>`, `<Navigate>`, and `<Link>`; no magic path strings in components.
- **Route guards** ‚Äî `components/routing/ProtectedRoute.tsx` (lazy `getMe` + redirect to login) and `GuestRoute.tsx` (redirect authenticated users to home).
- **Shared layout** ‚Äî colocate a layout next to the pages it serves (e.g. `pages/auth/AuthLayout.tsx`) and pass the form via `children`; do not duplicate the scene per page.
- Mutations (register/login) use component logic hooks calling RTK Query mutation hooks ‚Äî **no page-context `fetch*` layer** when there is no data to load.

## FE system hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/`) vs slice hooks (`hooks/slices/`)

- **System hooks** live directly under `apps/FE/src/hooks/` ‚Äî cross-cutting, non-slice utilities: `use-toast.ts`, `use-error.ts`, `use-success.ts`.
- **Slice hooks** live under `apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/` ‚Äî one per Redux slice (`useAuth.ts`), the typed facade over slice state + actions.
- Do **not** put slice facades under `hooks/` root, and do **not** put generic utilities under `hooks/slices/`.

## FE constants (`apps/FE/src/utils/constants/`)

- `utils/constants/` is a **directory**, not a flat `constants.ts` file:
  - `index.ts` ‚Äî barrel (keeps `@/utils/constants` imports working).
  - `axios.constants.ts` ‚Äî `AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`.
  - `routes.constants.ts` ‚Äî `FE_ROUTES` (`HOME`, `LOGIN`, `SIGNUP`, `LOGOUT`), `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`.
  - `toast-variants.constants.ts` ‚Äî `TOAST_VARIANTS = { SUCCESS, WARNING, ERROR }`.
- Add new constant groups as `*.constants.ts` files re-exported from the barrel ‚Äî do not reintroduce a single flat file.

## FE toast variants

- Classic **shadcn toast** (Radix `@radix-ui/react-toast`), **not** `sonner` ‚Äî typed `cva` `toastVariants` + reducer queue that `use-error` / `use-success` can drive.
- Variants: `default`, `success` (green), `warning` (amber), `error` (red / destructive); names centralized in `TOAST_VARIANTS`.
- `use-error` skips the generic network fallback message, fires the `error` variant for real API errors, then clears the slice error; `use-success` is the analogous success-message hook.
- Mount `<Toaster/>` once (in `app/app.tsx`).

## FE public assets (`apps/FE/public/`)

- Static assets (sprite sheets, etc.) live under `apps/FE/public/` and are served at the site root by Vite (e.g. `public/sprites/duckling.png` ‚Üí `/sprites/duckling.png`).
- Sprite/duck visuals: `public/sprites/` holds the walking-duck sheets (`duckling.png`, `mallard.png`); canvas components live in `components/duck/`.

## Backend routes (`libs/qu-constants/src/lib/be-routes.constants.ts`)

| Artifact | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| **`BE_ROUTES` enum** | API path segments shared via `@shared/constants` |

- Define **every** BE endpoint path segment in `be-routes.constants.ts` ‚Äî global prefix (`BASE`), controller segments (`USERS`, ‚Ä¶), and action segments (`SIGNUP`, ‚Ä¶).
- **No magic route strings** in controllers or `main.ts` ‚Äî use `BE_ROUTES` in `@Controller`, `@Get`/`@Post`/‚Ä¶, and `setGlobalPrefix`.
- Place in `qu-constants` so the FE can import the same segments for API clients later.

## Backend feature modules (`apps/BE/src/<feature>/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`<feature>.controller.ts`** | HTTP routes for the feature | `users/users.controller.ts` |
| **`<feature>.dto.ts`** | `createZodDto` wrappers for that feature‚Äôs Zod schemas | `users/users.dto.ts` ‚Üí `SignupDto` |
| **`<feature>.module.ts`** | Nest module wiring | `users/users.module.ts` |

- Colocate **DTO wrappers next to the controller** (`users/users.dto.ts`), not only in `app/app.dto.ts`.
- Shared Zod schemas stay in `libs/dtos`; BE wrappers import from `@shared/dtos`.

## Backend decorators (`apps/BE/src/decorators/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.decorator.ts`** | Nest param/method/class decorators shared across features | `current-user.decorator.ts` ‚Üí `@CurrentUser()` |

- Colocate reusable Nest decorators under `apps/BE/src/decorators/`, not inside feature folders (`auth/`, `users/`, ‚Ä¶).

## Backend utilities (`apps/BE/src/utils/`)

| Location | Purpose | Example |
| -------- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.util.ts`** | BE helpers (hashing, error parsing, ‚Ä¶) | `password.util.ts`, `mongoose-error.handler.util.ts` |
| **`libs/<service>/`** | Wrappers for **external services** (S3, logger, email, ‚Ä¶) | `utils/libs/s3/` |

- Do not use bare `utils/foo.ts` ‚Äî use the **`.util.ts`** suffix.
- External SDK clients belong under `utils/libs/<domain-name-for-service>/`, not at `utils/` root.

## Imports

- `@shared/dtos`, `@shared/constants` from apps and `mongoose/`
- **`@quack/mongoose/*`** ‚Äî repo Mongoose layer (`mongoose/` at repo root). **Do not** use deep relative imports (e.g. `../../../../mongoose/...`) or bare `mongoose/...` paths that collide with the npm `mongoose` package.
- App-local: `@/*` under `apps/FE` or `apps/BE`
- App tsconfigs: `baseUrl: "../.."` and extend `./tsconfig.json` (FE must keep `jsx`)

